            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>Lucius Calpurnius Fabatus, son of Lucius, of Oufentina tribe, sexvir, quattuorvir with judicial authority, prefect of engineers, tribune twice of the 21st legion Rapax, prefect of the 7th cohort of Lusitanian auxiliaries, and of six Gaetulian tribal units which were in Numidia, flamen of the divine Augustus, patron of the municipium, he ordered (this monument) to be made in his will.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>This Lucius Calpurnius Fabatus, flamen of the divine Augustus, is mentioned in Tacitus (Ann. 16.8) and is grandfather of Pliny the Younger's third wife, Calpurnia, to whom Pliny the Younger addresses nine letters (4.1, 5.11, 6.12, 6.30, 7.11, 7.16, 7.23, 8.10).</p> 
            </div>
